1) cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image retrieval tasks and proposes a deep architecture for supervised hashing using convolutional neural networks. 
2) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper involves learning features and encoding them into binary codes using deep neural networks. 
3) cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible category as the paper deals with nearest neighbor search in large-scale image retrieval tasks. 
4) cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with image retrieval tasks and proposes a deep architecture for supervised hashing. 
5) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper involves the use of deep neural networks for feature learning and hash coding.
